The cup circulated from left to right, not, as with ns, from right to left. The guests at a Roman dinner reclined on three couches, plaoed at three tables; two of the couches (lecti) were par- allel, and the third was at right angles to the other two. The lectus at which the cup began to circulate was summus, the next medius, the last imus. For a summo cf. da (sc. bibere) a summo in Plaut. Asin. 5, 2, 41.
